Governor Aminu Masari of Katsina State on Tuesday implored the Nigerian Air Force and the Nigerian Army to deploy modern technology in tackling terrorism and other related crimes in the country. He made the appeal in Katsina State while receiving the Air Officer commanding Special Operations Command, AVM Tajudeen Yusuf. The governor also called for more synergy among various security agencies in the country to effectively tackle insecurity. The governor observed that the huge unutilised land mass in the North served as hiding places for terrorists. He added that terrorists have been in the forests for years. Masari explained that his administration inaugurated “three-tier traditional security structure committees” in the three senatorial zones of the State to tackle insecurity and restore peace in the state. AVM Yusuf, had earlier in his remarks, explained that he was in the state to ensure that peace is restored not only in Katsina but also throughout the country. AVM Yusuf also told the governor that his visit was to interact with the officers and men of the Nigerian Airforce and inform them “that the authority was well pleased with their conduct as well as to encourage them to do more in order to achieve the desired aim in a very short time.”